<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="593" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Governor Sir <persName type="from">W.
                                    MacGregor</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Earl of
                                    Elgin</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Downing
                                        Street</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-17"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Referring to your telegram of the 16th August, please send brief summary
                            of your ministers’ reply to me by telegraph.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>